#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:0
msgid "# Vector 算子开发"
msgstr "# Vector Operator Development"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:2
msgid "Vector 算子主要由 Vector Core 执行，典型形态包括逐元素计算、行级归约、类型转换、Gather/Scatter、Mask 更新以及不含 `tl.dot` 的小型融合算子。开发重点不是把 grid 切得越细越好，而是在固定物理 Vector Core 数量的前提下，让每个 program 在核内循环处理多个 tile。"
msgstr "The Vector operator is primarily executed by the Vector Core, with typical forms including element-wise computation, row-level reduction, type conversion, Gather/Scatter, Mask updates, and small fused operators that do not involve `tl.dot`. The development focus is not on making the grid as fine-grained as possible, but rather on having each program process multiple tiles in a loop within the core, given a fixed number of physical Vector Cores."

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:4
msgid "## Vector 简单算子开发"
msgstr "## Vector Simple Operator Development"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:6
msgid "简单 Vector 算子可以从本仓的 [向量相加样例](../examples/01_vector_add_example.md) 或 `third_party/ascend/tutorials/01-vector-add.py` 入手。该类算子的基本步骤如下："
msgstr "Simple Vector operators can start from the [vector addition example](../examples/01_vector_add_example.md) in this repository or `third_party/ascend/tutorials/01-vector-add.py`. The basic steps for this type of operator are as follows:"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:8
msgid ""
"1. 用 `tl.arange` 构造当前 tile 的连续偏移。\n"
"2. 用 `mask` 保护尾块，避免越界 load/store。\n"
"3. 完成逐元素计算后写回结果。\n"
"4. 当 grid 数远大于物理核数时，将 grid 固定为 `num_vectorcore`，在 kernel 内用 `range(pid, num_blocks, num_core)` 分批处理。\n"
msgstr ""
"1. Use `tl.arange` to construct the contiguous offsets of the current tile.\n"
"2. Use `mask` to protect the tail block and prevent out-of-bounds load/store.\n"
"3. After completing the element-wise computation, write back the results.\n"
"4. When the number of grids is much larger than the number of physical cores, fix the grid to `num_vectorcore` and process in batches within the kernel using `range(pid, num_blocks, num_core)`.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:10
msgid "基础 kernel 结构如下："
msgstr "The basic kernel structure is as follows:"

#. type: code
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:12
msgid ""
"```python\n"
"@triton.jit\n"
"def add_kernel(x_ptr, y_ptr, out_ptr, n_elements, BLOCK_SIZE: tl.constexpr):\n"
"    pid = tl.program_id(0)\n"
"    num_core = tl.num_programs(0)\n"
"    num_blocks = tl.cdiv(n_elements, BLOCK_SIZE)\n"
"\n"
"    for block_idx in range(pid, num_blocks, num_core):\n"
"        offsets = block_idx * BLOCK_SIZE + tl.arange(0, BLOCK_SIZE)\n"
"        mask = offsets < n_elements\n"
"        x = tl.load(x_ptr + offsets, mask=mask)\n"
"        y = tl.load(y_ptr + offsets, mask=mask)\n"
"        tl.store(out_ptr + offsets, x + y, mask=mask)\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:14
msgid "开发时优先检查三类问题："
msgstr "Prioritize checking three types of issues during development:"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:16
msgid ""
"- **数据类型**：Ascend Vector 单元对不同整数类型的支持和性能不同。对于不影响精度的索引、长度、偏移类数据，优先使用 `int32`，可参考 `triton-ascend-ops/tutorial/basic/001-vector_add.zh.md` 和 `002-vector_cmp.zh.md`。\n"
"- **BLOCK_SIZE**：BLOCK_SIZE 需要在 UB 容量内尽量大。若出现 UB overflow，先降低单次处理元素数，再考虑拆分子块。\n"
"- **分核数**：NPU 物理 Vector Core 数量通常为几十个。小 tile 大 grid 的 GPU 写法迁移到 NPU 时，容易因多轮下发带来明显开销。\n"
msgstr ""
"- **Data Types**: Ascend Vector units have different support and performance for various integer types. For index, length, and offset data that do not affect precision, prefer using `int32`. Refer to `triton-ascend-ops/tutorial/basic/001-vector_add.zh.md` and `002-vector_cmp.zh.md`.\n"
"- **BLOCK_SIZE**: BLOCK_SIZE should be as large as possible within the UB capacity. If UB overflow occurs, first reduce the number of elements processed per iteration, then consider splitting sub-blocks.\n"
"- **Number of Cores**: The number of physical Vector Cores on an NPU is typically in the tens. When migrating GPU code with small tiles and large grids to NPU, multiple rounds of dispatch can easily introduce significant overhead.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:18
msgid "## Vector 复杂算子开发"
msgstr "## Vector Complex Operator Development"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:20
msgid "复杂 Vector 算子通常不是单个逐元素表达式，而是带有离散访存、批量重排、多个输出或长 hidden size 的组合逻辑。可参考 [Ascend/triton-ascend-ops](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops) 中的以下案例："
msgstr "Complex Vector operators are typically not single element-wise expressions, but rather combinatorial logic involving discrete memory access, batch rearrangement, multiple outputs, or long hidden sizes. Refer to the following examples in [Ascend/triton-ascend-ops](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops):"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:22
msgid ""
"- [`tutorial/best_practice/004-gather_scatter.py`](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops/blob/main/tutorial/best_practice/004-gather_scatter.py)：Megablocks gather/scatter/scatter_wgrad 的 Ascend 亲和实现。\n"
"- [`tutorial/best_practice/005-binned_gather_scatter.py`](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops/blob/main/tutorial/best_practice/005-binned_gather_scatter.py)：按 expert/bin 分组后的 gather/scatter。\n"
"- [`tutorial/best_practice/006-padded_gather_scatter.py`](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops/blob/main/tutorial/best_practice/006-padded_gather_scatter.py)：带 padding 的 MoE gather/scatter。\n"
msgstr ""
"- [`tutorial/best_practice/004-gather_scatter.py`](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops/blob/main/tutorial/best_practice/004-gather_scatter.py): Ascend-friendly implementation of Megablocks gather/scatter/scatter_wgrad.\n"
"- [`tutorial/best_practice/005-binned_gather_scatter.py`](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops/blob/main/tutorial/best_practice/005-binned_gather_scatter.py): Gather/scatter after grouping by expert/bin.\n"
"- [`tutorial/best_practice/006-padded_gather_scatter.py`](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops/blob/main/tutorial/best_practice/006-padded_gather_scatter.py): MoE gather/scatter with padding.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:24
msgid "这类算子的组织方式通常是："
msgstr "The organization of this type of operator is usually:"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:26
msgid ""
"1. **按物理核切分外层任务**：用 `num_vectorcore` 作为 grid，每个 program 负责一段 indices 或 token。\n"
"2. **按 UB 容量切分 hidden 维**：对 `NUM_COLUMNS` 使用 `BLOCK_X` 分块，并预留 double buffer、索引和临时张量的空间。\n"
"3. **用 `SUB_BLOCK_SIZE` 合并小粒度离散任务**：一次加载一组 indices，在 UB 中组织成连续临时块，减少 GM 标量访存和多次 store。\n"
"4. **用扩展语义管理 UB 内局部数据**：先通过 `import triton.language.extra.cann.extension as extension` 引入扩展模块，再使用 `extension.insert_slice` 合并多行数据，使用 `extension.extract_slice` 取出子块后再分散写回。\n"
"5. **为尾块保留统一 mask**：复杂 gather/scatter 中同时存在 index mask、column mask 和 expert/bin 边界，建议分别命名并只在 load/store 处组合。\n"
msgstr ""
"1. **Partition outer tasks by physical cores**: Use `num_vectorcore` as the grid, with each program responsible for a segment of indices or tokens.\n"
"2. **Partition the hidden dimension by UB capacity**: Apply `BLOCK_X` to chunk `NUM_COLUMNS`, reserving space for double buffers, indices, and temporary tensors.\n"
"3. **Merge small-grained discrete tasks using `SUB_BLOCK_SIZE`**: Load a group of indices at once, organize them into contiguous temporary blocks in UB, reducing GM scalar memory access and multiple stores.\n"
"4. **Manage local data within UB using extended semantics**: First import the extension module via `import triton.language.extra.cann.extension as extension`, then use `extension.insert_slice` to merge multiple rows of data, and use `extension.extract_slice` to extract sub-blocks before scattering writes.\n"
"5. **Reserve a unified mask for tail blocks**: In complex gather/scatter operations, index masks, column masks, and expert/bin boundaries coexist. It is recommended to name them separately and combine them only at load/store points.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:28
msgid "典型的 UB 预算思路如下："
msgstr "A typical UB budget approach is as follows:"

#. type: code
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:30
msgid ""
"```python\n"
"num_core = get_npu_properties()[\"num_vectorcore\"]\n"
"block_size = triton.cdiv(indices_length, num_core)\n"
"align_elems = 16\n"
"block_x = triton.cdiv(min(num_columns, max_block_x), align_elems) * align_elems\n"
"sub_block_size = max((ub_budget - block_x * element_bytes) //\n"
"                     (block_x * element_bytes + index_bytes), 1)\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:32
msgid "当复杂 Vector 算子性能不达预期时，优先从以下方向排查："
msgstr "When the performance of a complex Vector operator does not meet expectations, prioritize troubleshooting from the following directions:"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/vector_operator.md:34
msgid ""
"- grid 是否远大于物理 Vector Core 数，导致多轮下发。\n"
"- 离散访存是否可转化为“批量搬入 UB 后在 UB 内选择”。\n"
"- 尾轴是否满足 32B 对齐；不满足时是否可用转置或借轴转置规避自动 padding。\n"
"- `BLOCK_X` 和 `SUB_BLOCK_SIZE` 是否造成 UB overflow 或过小的搬运粒度。\n"
msgstr ""
"- Whether the grid is much larger than the number of physical Vector Cores, causing multiple rounds of dispatch.\n"
"- Whether discrete memory access can be transformed into \"batch load into UB and then select within UB\".\n"
"- Whether the tail axis satisfies 32B alignment; if not, whether transpose or borrowing axis transpose can be used to avoid automatic padding.\n"
"- Whether `BLOCK_X` and `SUB_BLOCK_SIZE` cause UB overflow or excessively small transfer granularity.\n"

